probejs.already_running: There's already a dumping thread running, please wait.
probejs.dump.decompiling: Decompiling mods, this might take some time...
probejs.dump.class_discovered: Discovered %s classes to generate typing for.
probejs.dump.dump_finished: The typing generation of script type %s is finished.
probejs.dump.dump_error: Dump generation of script type %s failed, this might be a bug in code.
probejs.dump.cleaning: Removing old dump files that might contain invalid classes... This can be slow.
probejs.hello: Welcome to ProbeJS! An automatic dump will be triggered everytime you enter the game with some new stuffs!
probejs.enabled_warning: ProbeJS is enabled! You should exclude .probe generated when you finished development, and disable the mod by:
probejs.bye_bye: ProbeJS is now disabled. require() still works, though. Don't forget to exclude the typing.
probejs.hello_again: ProbeJS is enabled now. Happy coding!
probejs.isolation: ProbeJS will isolate each script files now, only `export`ed identifiers will be exposed.
probejs.no_isolation: ProbeJS will not try to isolate different scopes now. Be aware of duplicated names.
probejs.wiki: To learn about how to use ProbeJS (or report issue), please go to the
probejs.interactive: ProbeJS interactive server is listening on port %s.
probejs.complete: ProbeJS will dump all the complex types now, at expense of VSCode performance.
probejs.no_complete: ProbeJS will disable some types in dump now, so your VSCode should run faster. Use snippets for those types missing.
probejs.performance: You installed %s mods! Some functions are disabled for the sake of performance, but probably not much.
probejs.decompile: ProbeJS will decompile mod sources at next dump, decompilation will also trigger when mod list changed.
probejs.no_decompile: ProbeJS will not decompile mod sources now.
